Stenoma heteroxantha is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1931. It is found in Paraguay and Brazil.
The wingspan is 16â€“17 mm. The forewings are orange yellow, with the costal edge whitish and the stigmata small, indistinct and violet brownish, the plical obliquely beyond the first discal. There are rather small violet-brownish spots on the costa at the middle and three-fourths, and on the tornus. The hindwings are pale grey or whitish grey.